⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of West Canaan, Texas
node VBL · VBL · ⟦West Canaan, Texas:VBL:4ee145⟧

WHO   — West Canaan, Texas — the town that worships Friday
WHAT  — Friday-night faith: the real American thing the film is built on (the nonfiction version is Friday Night Lights).
WHERE — VBL · Varsity Blues (1999)  Framework inputs: Varsity Blues (1999, dir. Brian Robbins, MTV Films/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the town is the real villain's accomplice: it worships the winning enough to look away from the cost.
HOW   — By making football the only religion, the only economy, and the only door — so the coach can do anything as long as he wins.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am a whole town's identity riding on seventeen-year-olds on a Friday — and I will forgive any sin that ends in a W.

